# Frontend Next.js + TypeScript Standards

Apply these rules when editing frontend code.

- Use strict typing and keep interfaces aligned with backend C++ payloads/JSON.
- Separate business logic from presentation:
  - logic in hooks/services
  - UI in components
- Prefer App Router patterns and keep data flow explicit.
- Use Server Actions for server-side data mutations/fetching where appropriate.
- Use WebSocket/Fetch patterns consistently for real-time sensor data.

## Quality Expectations

- Keep component boundaries clear and avoid leaking transport details into UI.
- Add/update tests when behavior or contracts change.
- Favor small, maintainable refactors over broad rewrites.
